caption.text:
Shame If It Dropped On Somebody! - Stick Fight: The Game

@vanillapandausa (Playing as the yellow stick fighter) had a plan that backfired. White Bread as Red stick fighter & AGK Weeley as Blue stick fighter.
•
#stickfight #stickfightthegame #landfallwest #landfallgames #gaming #letsplay #livestream #gamer #twitch #twitchstreamer #gamer #instagamer #instagaming #game #games #gamers #gamingvideos #videogame #videogames #fightinggame #fightinggames #pcgame #pcgaming #pcgames #pcgamers

A week has past since I got back from New Zealand. The humid atmosphere was getting to me. I love studying abroad don't get me wrong, but I was happy to be back home.
Mom: Amanda, can you get out of bed please? It has been 4 hours since you woke up this morning. I made you breakfast and it is getting cold!
I slowly got out of bed with a big groan and my hair in a messier bun than what it was when I went to bed the night before. I jogged down the stairs and sat the table.
Mom: I made you eggs and bacon, and of course your favorite coffee.
Dark roast with half and half. My favorite coffee. I have it every morning, noon, and night. It is what keeps me going. As I eat my mom tells me what is going to get done today. Burning the fields. I live in Jorvik, near everwind fields. While everyone else lives and boards at fancy riding centers I live on a 42 acre ranch. Livestock and all! I love it. But it is a lot of work. My whole family pitches in, so it is a great bonding experience for all of us. I eat my food quickly, cold eggs and bacon is not the best. I put on my fire gear and grab my terrier Reed. People think terriers cant do much on the ranch. But if you are a cow and have a tiny 11lb rat dog running at you with sharp teeth, you are gonna move! As I step outside I notice the crisp air hitting my lips and eyes. I shiver a little since I am still use to New Zealand weather. But nonetheless I hop into my four wheeler and put my coffee in the cupholder and set Reed right next to me. I drove down to the first field as quick as I could. We burn the fields to create richer soil for the new harvest, I hate this time of the year but it is necessary since this is how my family makes money, through our crops. I  leave Reed in my four wheeler as I put on the rest of my heavy safety gear and hop into the truck that will be lighting the fire. I start the engine and get to work. I notice, about 15 minutes later, that Reed is missing from my four wheeler. My eyes widen in fear, the fire is spreading through the nearby field quickly. I turn off the truck and hop out. Adrenaline rushing through my body as I run looking for him. (Cont. in comments!)

Monday night board games! I much prefer this to having the TV on after dinner. Tonight we played #Photosynthesis, a game where you plant trees and they compete for the best light and soil conditions. The sun revolves around the board, you strategically distribute seeds and level-up your trees, then harvest them for bonus points depending on the soil quality. You don't have to love trees to love this game, but it's fantastic how it reflects true competition in nature. Definitely recommend to try if you ever get the chance!

Trevor thoughtfully picked this for me as his anniversary gift. It's made from 100% post-consumer recycled paper, so it counts to the "paper" theme for first anniversaries 😄

Today we are proud to move forward into the next stage of the Club's life. For the past year, Kyle Haddleton and Morgan Humphreys have worked hard to secure both the space and funding for a gaming hub on campus alongside @murdochsports. We are currently moving into the second phase due to a sizeable grant that got approved by the SSAF committee. The facility will give us a chance to allow our teams a dedicated space to train and organise more cross-university exhibition matches, plus more. The room is estimated to be open to students in February 2020. 
Being a part of facilitating @murdochuniversity recognition of Esports is both exciting and fills us personally with pride. We are sure the students are going to love the gaming hub. To state we are all excited for this project is an understatement; we can not wait to see what 2020 brings for the Club. We are sure we'll be supporting the universities stance on Esports for years to come. Feel free to tell us feedback regarding your hopes and dreams for the room so we can best represent you as the project moves forward.

Ni no Kuni: Wrath of the White Witch

It is a role-playing video game, developed by Level-5. It was released for the PlayStation 3 in Japan in November 2011, and published in Western regions by Namco Bandai Games in January 2013. It was also released for Nintendo Switch in September 2019, alongside a remastered version for Microsoft Windows and PlayStation 4. The game is a significantly enhanced version of Ni no Kuni: Dominion of the Dark Djinn, which originally released for the Nintendo DS in Japan in December 2010.

caption.text:
É extremamente comum em um jogo você ter vários aspectos que se repetem, inimigos, objetos no cenário, itens e etc. 
Por isso também é bastante comum nós podermos generalizar essas coisas e reutiliza-lás. …
Pegue o exemplo de um personagem principal, ele vai estar EM TODAS AS FASES! Kkkk
Agora imagine o fluxo -> Criar uma cena nova -> Colocar um SKSpriteNode -> Colocar a textura do personagem -> Seta as animações -> Os componentes -> Roda o jogo

Agora pense que seu jogo tem 30 fases distintas… Isso irá se repetir 30 vezes, kkkk. 
Pior… Na 27 fase você percebeu que a escala podia ser melhorada, aumentar só um pouquinho, você terá que voltar em cada fase e ajustar isso, certo?

Pois bem, chega de fazer as coisas no Go horsing… trago a vocês a tal solução…
SKReferenceNode
Esse lindo, é um node que simplesmente é uma referência a uma outra cena! Então numa cena podemos fazer o personagem principal e em todas as outras 30 só referenciaremos ela. Relaxa que não pesa já que é só uma referência!
E você também pode modificar a vontade dentro de uma cena específica se quiser algo especializado para tal cena, ou modificar na cena “mestre” e assim em todos os lugares que ela estiver sendo referenciada a modificação será aplicada! Show né?
